The paper focuses on using PlumX, an analytical tool, to analyze the impact of a large collection of books. This analysis involves various metrics such as usage counts, catalogue holdings, and reviews. These metrics are related to digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybernetics (cs.CY), social and information networks (cs.SI), and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
